    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-07T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-07T17:00:00-05:00" n="114"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d114">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/8</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-07T22:00:00+00:00">
                        <hi rend="italic">August 7, 1914, 10 p.m.</hi>
                    </date>
                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received August 8, 5 a.m.</hi>] </dateline>
                <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                <p>298. I have just come from a long conversation with <persName corresp="#p_GSE1"
                        >Sir Edward Grey</persName>. He explained at length why England went to war
                    only because war was forced upon her and therefore without any object except to
                    keep her faith and to preserve her place among the nations. She will welcome
                    mediation whenever a favorable time comes. If the war be brief, the chance may
                    come quickly. If it prove a long-drawn, equal struggle, a chance may come when
                    this fact becomes apparent. <persName corresp="#p_GSE1">Sir Edward</persName>
                    was most appreciative of the President’s offer and requested me to convey the
                    British Government’s thanks.</p>
                <closer>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Ambassador</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
